# AppTile

An AppTile is used to display basic information about an App the user can access. It renders a label and an icon related to the App.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/app-tile
```

```tsx
import { AppTile } from '@ids-ts/app-tile';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `label` | `string` | Yes | label text to render underneath the icon |
| `icon` | `React.ReactElement<IconProps>` | Yes | icon to render inside the tile |
| `product` | `Product` | No | what product this tile is displaying |
| `onClick` | `React.MouseEventHandler` | No | Callback when this tile is selected |
| `recommendation` | `boolean` | No | whether this tile is being used to recommend an App to the user |
| `animated` | `boolean` | No | whether to animate the size of this component when hovered. Defaults to true |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface AppTileProps extends ThemeableElement<'button'> {
  /** label text to render underneath the icon */
  label: string;
  /** icon to render inside the tile */
  icon: React.ReactElement<IconProps>;
  /** what product this tile is displaying */
  product?: Product;
  /** Callback when this tile is selected */
  onClick?: React.MouseEventHandler;
  /** whether this tile is being used to recommend an App to the user */
  recommendation?: boolean;
  /** whether to animate the size of this component when hovered. Defaults to true */
  animated?: boolean;
}

export type Product = 'intuit' | 'quickbooks' | 'turbotax' | 'mailchimp';
```

</details>

